Njoroge, If you are working in the tourism industry you need to be super alert. Corruption is lethal in all senses of that word.

Currently there are many opportunities for the average Kenyan to invest in real estate especially around the coast but due to greed people rush in without thinking. ( hold on I said greed due to not a lack of opportunity). I look at it like making investments. Let your money work for you not visa versa. We are privileged that we live in a climate conducive for holidays all year round. Many people spend all their lives saving money and but governments, Ministries, Departments and even individuals ruine them in 5 minutes. Take the time to do proper research, don't expect everybody to react to your case depending on the mood, organize your accounts properly on what you can afford to lose, don't listen too much to Hot air, Don't be quick to consolidate. We all want to be rich and feel we were cheated if we lose 100 bob. What are our painful experiences is other peoples opportunity. Be calculative and enjoy the adventure.

Well, if you were born in Kenya you are entitled to buy real estate there. Just don't make it land or it may get complicated
